                <td bgcolor="#5A71AD" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="white" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2">Masklinn</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#5A71AD" valign="top"><font color="white" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;10/13/2003&nbsp;: 03:54:24 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> 1- Affliction Focuses (DoTs only)<br />Burning Affliction: Increases DoT damage random 1-20%<br />Vengeance of Time: BA 25%<br />Affliction Haste: Spell Haste DoTs only, 33%<br />Affliction Efficiency: Mana Preservation DoTs only 25%<br />Extended Torment: Increase spell duration for 1-10% (detrimentals with a duration &gt; 24s only)<br /><br />2- General Focuses<br />Spell Haste: Hastes spell casting time 10%<br />Other hastes can be found, they range from 15 to 2X% haste (Solusek hastes are for detrimental spells only)<br />Improved Damage: Higher the amout of damage done by your DDs, random 1-15% i think<br />Other IDs:<br />Solusek can go up to 25%<br />Druzzil ID's are for Magic based DDs only (ToM and Destroy Undead), they go from 21 to 35% (Anger to Fury i think)<br />Mana Preservation: 1-10% cut in the mana cost of your spells<br />Once again you can get other preservations, like Focus of Solusek or Preservation of Xegony<br />Extended Range: Highers your casting range (usually 200 for detrimental spells) by a fixed amount, i myself think of these focuses as "godly"<br />Other Xrange focuses: Starfall Symbol, Druzzil's Range<br /><br />3- Other Focuses<br />Sanguine Preservation: Mana Preservation self buffs only 40%<br /><br />Be careful: if you're in VT, focuses almost never bear a recognizable name (they will be named Accursed Extention or Insidious Dreams), go to <a href="http://lucy.fnord.net" target="_blank">http://lucy.fnord.net</a> if you need informations on a focus</span></font></td>
